# PyInstaller
#  Usually these files are located in the same folder as the script
#  and are not tracked by version control.
# .idea/ is a common file generated by PyCharm and should be ignored
# for all team members. The official documentation has more on this
# at https://www.jetbrains.com/help/pycharm/set-up-a-git-repository.html
# for all team members.
#
# .venv/ and env/ are common names for virtual environment directories
# and should be ignored for all team members.
#
# .env files often contain sensitive information like API keys and
# should always be ignored for security reasons, as discussed by
# FreeCodeCamp at https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/gitignore-what-is-it-and-how-to-add-to-repo/.
#
# Note: If a file has already been committed to your repository,
# adding it to .gitignore will not untrack it. You will need to
# untrack it manually using git rm --cached [filename], as noted
# by Graphite at 

